<div id="empty_slate_milestones_milestones" class="empty_slate">
  <h3>{lang}About Milestones{/lang}</h3>
  <ul class="icon_list">
    <li>
      <img src="{image_url name=admin/whatis.gif}" class="icon_list_icon" alt="" />
      <span class="icon_list_title">{lang}Milestones Mark Key Points in a Project{/lang}</span>
      <span class="icon_list_description">{lang}Milestones mark key points in a project so you can have a bird-eye view over things that needs to be done, when and who is responsible. Milestone can be a single day event or a time period with start and due date. When you need more details, you can click on a milestone's name to "zoom in" and see all related discussions, files and tasks{/lang}.</span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <img src="{image_url name=admin/calendar.gif}" class="icon_list_icon" alt="" />
      <span class="icon_list_title">{lang}Keep Your Calendar Application in Sync with Milestones{/lang}</span>
      <span class="icon_list_description">{lang}If you want to have milestones synchronized with calendars in your favorite calendar application (iCal, Outlook 2007, Google Calendar), then subscribe to iCalendar feed provided by the system. On the Calendar page you can find global feed with milestones and tasks from all active projects. The system also provides a feed for each project and you can find it by visiting overview page of the particular project{/lang}.</span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <img src="{image_url name=settings/mailing.gif module=system}" class="icon_list_icon" alt="" />
      <span class="icon_list_title">{lang}Email Notifications{/lang}</span>
      <span class="icon_list_description">{lang}Subscribe to a milestone to receive email notification when it is completed or reopened. The person responsible for the milestone can edit the list of subscribers using Manage Subscriptions tool (available from Options menu){/lang}.</span>
    </li>
  </ul>
</div>